content.description: Starts down low with both hands on the jug and moves up and to the right. Starts with slopey jugs that lead into some fun foot work, ends with a nice top out.
content.location: Parking is on Hunt Lane. Follow the main trail for 1/4 mile until you reach the intersection with the Old Sib trail (Marked O.S). Follow the Old Sib Trail up the hill and keep going for about 1/3 mile and you will see a large mossy boulder coming up on your left. You will find this boulder right after that on your right about 40 feet or so off the trail.

content.description: This area is off of the Old Sib hiking trail in the Northern tip of the Sal J Prezioso Mountain Lakes Park. There are a few decent sized boulders in this area but at the moment I have only found one that is climbable, most of them are covered in moss and lichen.
